{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2024/12/bpmn-orhcestrated-system-tests/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Asko Soukka","author":"Asko Soukka"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"b46ca511-ec5a-578d-b6f1-698d3a970ac1","fields":{"slug":"/2024/12/bpmn-orhcestrated-system-tests/"},"excerpt":"The battle between monoliths and microservices aside, in real life, even monolithic systems rarely operate in isolation; they run integrated with an ever…","html":"<p>The battle between monoliths and microservices aside, in real life, even monolithic systems rarely operate in isolation; they run integrated with an ever-growing number of internal and external systems. Therefore, testing these systems in isolation is not enough. <strong>Real system testing requires evaluating the business processes that depend on them.</strong> Our hypothesis is that business process automation tools, combined with BPMN 2.0 as a visual and executable modeling standard with features for every special case, could significantly enhance the testing changes for those systems.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/663b1/robot-framework.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 88.51351351351352%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Robot Framework\"\n        title=\"Robot Framework\"\n        src=\"/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/fcda8/robot-framework.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/12f09/robot-framework.png 148w,\n/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/e4a3f/robot-framework.png 295w,\n/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/fcda8/robot-framework.png 590w,\n/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/efc66/robot-framework.png 885w,\n/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/c83ae/robot-framework.png 1180w,\n/static/941b4b614bd3f48bb0e548a967b307cc/663b1/robot-framework.png 1313w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>With this mindset, <a href=\"https://noordsestern.medium.com/\">Markus Stahl</a> and yours truly, are offering a workshop <a href=\"https://robocon.io/program#live-orchestrating-complex-end-to-end-test-suites-with-visual-bpmn-process-models\">Orchestrating complex end-to-end test suites with visual BPMN process models</a> on the 12th of February 2025 in Helsinki at <a href=\"https://robocon.io\">RoboCon.io Helsinki 2025</a>. Interested? Register until the end of 2024 with the voucher code <code>END-OF-YEAR-15</code> for a 15 % discount (profits, if any, would support <a href=\"https://robotframework.org/foundation/\">Robot Framework Foundation</a>).</p>\n<h2>Why BPMN?</h2>\n<p><strong>BPMN</strong> stands for <strong>Business Process Model and Notation</strong>. It’s a graphical presentation standard for specifying business processes in business process models. BPMN is <strong>grounded in research on workflow patterns</strong> and is designed to express any workflow a process requires. Additionally, it provides a mapping between graphical representations and execution, enabling the creation of visually clear models for any automated process. <strong>Including test automation!</strong></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/cc6fe/example-simple.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 14.18918918918919%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Simple BPMN test flow\"\n        title=\"Simple BPMN test flow\"\n        src=\"/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/fcda8/example-simple.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/12f09/example-simple.png 148w,\n/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/e4a3f/example-simple.png 295w,\n/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/fcda8/example-simple.png 590w,\n/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/efc66/example-simple.png 885w,\n/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/c83ae/example-simple.png 1180w,\n/static/5093f6604fb16c91788d587f90cfb977/cc6fe/example-simple.png 1860w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Even traditional test flows make beautiful diagrams, but the more challenging the flow, the more BPMN excels.</p>\n<p><strong>What if test suites take a long time to complete because they are waiting for external services?</strong></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/91306/example-poll.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 36.486486486486484%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Example BPMN test flow polling for external services\"\n        title=\"Example BPMN test flow polling for external services\"\n        src=\"/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/fcda8/example-poll.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/12f09/example-poll.png 148w,\n/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/e4a3f/example-poll.png 295w,\n/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/fcda8/example-poll.png 590w,\n/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/efc66/example-poll.png 885w,\n/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/c83ae/example-poll.png 1180w,\n/static/48e49531a9ab15f1dc71f7cfde66e567/91306/example-poll.png 3120w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>What if they take days due to waiting for third parties to complete their tasks?</strong></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/91306/example-conversation.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.72972972972973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Example BPMN test waiting for external events\"\n        title=\"Example BPMN test waiting for external events\"\n        src=\"/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/fcda8/example-conversation.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/12f09/example-conversation.png 148w,\n/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/e4a3f/example-conversation.png 295w,\n/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/fcda8/example-conversation.png 590w,\n/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/efc66/example-conversation.png 885w,\n/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/c83ae/example-conversation.png 1180w,\n/static/ca0540e1aaeb40108d4b9e06eae8745c/91306/example-conversation.png 3120w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>Or what if test suites require manual feedback or other forms of human interaction to finish?</strong></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/a2b91/example-manual.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.13513513513513%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Example BPMN test flow requiring manual tasks\"\n        title=\"Example BPMN test flow requiring manual tasks\"\n        src=\"/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/fcda8/example-manual.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/12f09/example-manual.png 148w,\n/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/e4a3f/example-manual.png 295w,\n/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/fcda8/example-manual.png 590w,\n/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/efc66/example-manual.png 885w,\n/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/c83ae/example-manual.png 1180w,\n/static/7f7b119c10b0af60e6896934bb8a6cb3/a2b91/example-manual.png 3360w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>What about when test flows become very complex due to parallel processes and conditional suites?</strong></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/d25be/example-complex.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Example complex BPMN test flow\"\n        title=\"Example complex BPMN test flow\"\n        src=\"/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/fcda8/example-complex.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/12f09/example-complex.png 148w,\n/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/e4a3f/example-complex.png 295w,\n/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/fcda8/example-complex.png 590w,\n/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/efc66/example-complex.png 885w,\n/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/c83ae/example-complex.png 1180w,\n/static/88d9461a62b0b215b3093515595a18fe/d25be/example-complex.png 3180w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>Yet, BPMN can make even the most complex test setups look simple and elegant:</strong></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/d25be/example-features.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Example test flow using sophisticated BPMN features\"\n        title=\"Example test flow using sophisticated BPMN features\"\n        src=\"/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/fcda8/example-features.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/12f09/example-features.png 148w,\n/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/e4a3f/example-features.png 295w,\n/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/fcda8/example-features.png 590w,\n/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/efc66/example-features.png 885w,\n/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/c83ae/example-features.png 1180w,\n/static/969811d9fef64b9747e3776c2a4dd774/d25be/example-features.png 3180w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Why workshop?</h2>\n<p>Didn’t understand all the symbols used in the previous diagrams? Don’t worry! If you’re able to attend <a href=\"https://robocon.io/program#live-orchestrating-complex-end-to-end-test-suites-with-visual-bpmn-process-models\">our workshop at RoboCon 2025 Helsinki</a>, everything should become clear. And if you can’t make it, we’ll do our best to publish all the materials shortly afterward.</p>\n<p>But modeling is just the beginning. A powerful open-source BPMN engine may rival traditional CI orchestration tools in many use cases. And it doesn’t have to stop at testing. As many test automation engineers know: if something can be automatically tested in development, it can often be automatically executed in production too.</p>\n<p>The same open-source BPMN setup we use in the workshop for test execution can also be applied to more traditional business process and task automation. BPMN-based orchestration doesn’t need to be a secret of the few. Let’s democratize it!</p>\n<p><strong>See you in February!</strong> <a href=\"https://robocon.io/\">At RoboCon 2025 Helsinki.</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/86177/operaton.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.16216216216216%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Operaton in operation\"\n        title=\"Operaton in operation\"\n        src=\"/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/fcda8/operaton.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/12f09/operaton.png 148w,\n/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/e4a3f/operaton.png 295w,\n/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/fcda8/operaton.png 590w,\n/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/efc66/operaton.png 885w,\n/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/c83ae/operaton.png 1180w,\n/static/93ab35d5206af2bed0beca9ef2b2e6ce/86177/operaton.png 2869w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"BPMN orchestrated end-to-end system testing with Robot Framework","tags":["Operaton","BPMN","Robot Framework","system testing","Open Source"],"date":"December 14, 2024","published":"2024-12-14 12:00:00"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2024/12/bpmn-orhcestrated-system-tests/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2023/04/diy-zeebe-dashboards/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"DIY Zeebe Applications"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2024/12/orchestrating-robot-framework/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Five ways to orchestrate Robot Framework execution with BPM engine"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}